{"lemma":"صَلْصالُ","slug":"صَلْصالُ","root":"ص.ل.ص.ل","root_slug":"ص-ل-ص-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ل-ص-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَلْصال","root":"صلصل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24668"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clay; argil","examples":[{"text":"خَلَقَ الْإِنْسَانَ مِن صَلْصَالٍ كَالْفَخَّارِ / وَخَلَقَ الجَانَّ مِنْ مَارِجٍ مِنْ نَارٍ","english":"Man, He made out of argil, like pottery. / Spirits, He made out of a blaze of fire."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clay; argil; any substance that may be worked and shaped like clay (like playdough); modeling clay"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sticky sand-mixed earth; loam","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sticky sand-mixed earth; loam; Sticky soft clay: that is used to make pottery, chinaware, and sculpted artifacts; sculpting clay","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Unknown. Has been compared to Old Armenian շաղեմ (šałem, “to knead or mix e.g. mortar”), շաղախ (šałax, “clay, mud, mortar”)."},"ipa":["/sˤal.sˤaːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24668","headword_ar":"صَلْصَالٌ","root":"Sl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noisy"},{"kind":"text","text":"ass; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuloSulN","text_ar":"صُلْصُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SulaASilN","text_ar":"صُلَاصِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSaloSilN","text_ar":"مُصَلْصِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) an ass"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong in voice"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bray"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Ahmad El-'Askeree, TA.) And A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp and slender"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrill"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in voice"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neigh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, TA.) And A wild ass"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp in voice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAl~N","text_ar":"صَالٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says Aboo-Ahmad El-Askeree: and thus is expl. the saying in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atuHib~uwna A^ano","text_ar":"اَتُحِبُّونَ اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takuwnuwA mivola AlHamiyri AlS~aAl~api","text_ar":"تَكُونُوا مِثْلَ الحَمِيرِ الصَّالَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would ye love to be like the asses"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound in bodies, vehement in voices, by reason of their strength and their briskness?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clay not made into pottery;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) so called because of its making a sound ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litaSaloSulihi","text_ar":"لِتَصَلْصُلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay mixed with sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, when it becomes dry, makes a sound; and which, when baked, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fax~aAr","text_ar":"فَخَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry clay, that makes a sound by reason of its dryness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, O, TA:) thus in the Kur lv. 13 [and xv. 26 and 28 and 33]: or, accord. to Mujáhid,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaA^N masonuwnN","text_ar":"حَمَاٌ مَسْنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black mud altered for the worse in odour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaloSaAlapN","text_ar":"صَلْصَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land in which is no one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","O","Z","TA"]}]}}